-----Original Message-----
From: seekerslady@...
[mailto:seekerslady@...]
Sent: Wednesday, July 28, 1999 7:12 PM
To: EQCheats@onelist.com
Subject: RE: [EQCheats] Level times

From: seekerslady@...

I used to play meridian 59. I loved this
game but people got burned out on
it becuase you could build too fast and then
got bored. Then people went
around and PKed each other. It turned a
wonderful online community into a
garbage dump. What is your great hurry? You
planning on leaving soon? As
long as you are having fun and meeting new
people and playing a game you
like what difference does it make what level
you are or how fast you get
there. These games are ment to be played for
years not weeks. I am
surprised that people have already been able
to max out. Now what do they
have to do? Ok they can go anywhere and kill
almost anything but how long
before they get bored and move on? The game
has only been out a few months.

Just my 2 cents

Feather Dreamwalker of Rathe
>
>I agree that level gaining is quite slow.
8-10 hours
>for a level is a bit much. I can't imagine
the high
>30s and above.
>
>Belgarth
